## Step 4: Create GitHub Repository

1. Go to https://github.com/new
2. Repository name: `shanghai-trip`
3. Description: "Shanghai & Suzhou Travel Itinerary"
4. Set to **Public**
5. Do NOT initialize with README
6. Click "Create repository"

## Step 5: Push Files to GitHub

Open PowerShell in the website folder and run:

```powershell
# Navigate to website folder
cd "C:\Users\14507183\.gemini\antigravity\brain\ff88d5d3-1ada-49f6-a98c-54429a49f07e\website"

# Initialize Git
git init

# Add all files
git add .

# Commit
git commit -m "Initial commit - Shanghai & Suzhou travel website"

# Add remote (replace zarppy with your username)
git remote add origin https://github.com/zarppy/shanghai-trip.git

# Push to GitHub
git push -u origin main
```

## Step 6: Enable GitHub Pages

1. Go to your repository: `https://github.com/zarppy/shanghai-trip`
2. Click **Settings**
3. Scroll to **Pages** (left sidebar)
4. Under "Source", select:
   - Branch: `main`
   - Folder: `/ (root)`
5. Click **Save**

## Step 7: Access Your Website

Your site will be live at:
```
https://zarppy.github.io/shanghai-trip/
```

It may take 2-3 minutes to build. Refresh the GitHub Pages settings to see the status.

## Testing Locally First

Before deploying, test locally:

1. Open PowerShell in the website folder
2. Run a simple HTTP server:
   ```powershell
   python -m http.server 8000
   ```
3. Open browser to: `http://localhost:8000`
4. Test the map and navigation

## Troubleshooting

### Images not showing?
- Check that images are in the `images/` folder
- Verify image paths in [index.html](file:///C:/Users/14507183/.gemini/antigravity/brain/ff88d5d3-1ada-49f6-a98c-54429a49f07e/website/index.html) start with `images/`

### Map not loading?
- Check browser console (F12) for errors
- Ensure [data/locations.json](file:///C:/Users/14507183/.gemini/antigravity/brain/ff88d5d3-1ada-49f6-a98c-54429a49f07e/website/data/locations.json) exists

### Site not publishing?
- Wait 2-3 minutes after enabling Pages
- Check GitHub Actions tab for build status
- Ensure repository is public

